<TITLE> Moeen promises hand in developing football </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 9 (bdnews24.com)  Chairman of the National Sports Council and Army Chief Moeen U Ahmed promised Bangladesh Football Federation officials Monday he would extend all help to develop the popular sport in the country. The pledge was made as the newly elected BFF executive committee, led by its president Kazi Salahuddin, had its first meeting with the NSC boss at the Bangladesh Olympic Association conference room. "He has promised us that he will try his best to develop football if needed," Salahuddin said of Moeen after the meeting. The new BFF committee was elected on April 18. Of a 21-member committee, 15 were present on the occasion. BOA secretary general Kutub Uddin Ahmed was also present. The former football superstar, Salahuddin, was optimistic on hearing the NSC chairman's comment on football. "It was a fine discussion with the chairman, who is well aware of the situation of Bangladesh football, and we let him know how we want to start," said the former national footballer. The NSC chairman told us that he would appoint more such sport-loving organisers, who would keep football rolling at district levels, said Salahuddin. General Moeen, also president of the Bangladesh Olympic Association, expressed his disappointed over the booters' performance in the SAFF Championship, but he did not blame the newly committee for the failure. "He asked us to note down from where we started, and where we want to go in the next four years," said Salahuddin. bdne
